The paper deals with distance computation in planar graphs, which is a fundamental problem in computer science. The paper introduces a new approach for distributed distance computation in planar graphs that significantly improves the state of the art. This suggests that the paper is likely to be classified under cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.CG (Computational Geometry). The paper also uses compression schemes, which suggests that it may be classified under cs.IT (Information Theory) and cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing). Finally, the paper presents distributed algorithms, which suggests that it may be classified under cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture).
